The paper proposes a novel method for motion planning of quadrotors using deep reinforcement learning. The focus is on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as the method uses deep learning techniques. The use of raw depth images suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also relevant. The paper also mentions the use of smooth motion primitives, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) may be relevant. Finally, the paper deals with navigation in cluttered environments, which suggests that systems and control (cs.SY) may also be relevant.
